      <bioghist id="aspace_6cf350b2abd2e1aea3b3d367856d8f61">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Yale Bibliophiles (ca. 1974-1990) were a group of individuals associated with Yale University who were interested in books and book arts. The group served the interests of its members by arranging trips, lectures, dicussions, and promoting the study of books and book arts.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_2a081f89bc888a7e41d8cbe833327d9a">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of newsletters, membership information, and promotional materials documenting the activities of the Yale Bibliophiles.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_e8dc86cda486a9a3250744e4aec9a5db">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by topic</p>
